ARTICLE 3 CONTRACT SUM
§ 3.1 The Contract Sum shall include all items and services necessary for the proper execution and completion of
the Work. Subject to additions and deductions in accordance with Article 10, the Contract Sum is:
Six Thousand Five Hundred Ninety-Five Dollars ($6,595)
§ 3.1.1 Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, the original Contract Sum set forth in Section 4.1 is not
subject to audit by the Owner and the Owner hereby waives its right to inspect the Contractor’s books and records
with respect to the costs encompassed under the original Contract Sum, except to the extent related to any sales tax
exemption. To preserve such confidentiality, for all payment applications seeking reimbursement under the original
Contract Sum, the Owner will receive lien waivers in dollar format from the Contractor and in percentage format
from the Subcontractors and vendors.
§ 3.1.2 Change Order Markups
For additive Changes in the Work as provided in Article 10 in addition to reimbursement for the net increase in
direct subcontracted costs and any self-performed work approved by the Owner (“Direct Work Increase”), the
Contractor shall be reimbursed as follows:
(a) General Conditions shall be ten (10%) of the Direct Work Increase (excluding the portion of Direct Work related
to self-performed work) (the “General Conditions Increase”; together with the Direct Work Increase, the “Cost of
the Work Increase”);
(b) Contractor’s Fee shall be two and three-quarters percent (2.75%) of the Cost of the Work Increase; and
(c) general liability insurance shall be at the rate of one and ninety-seven hundredths’ percent (1.97%) of the Cost of
the Work Increase and Fee (such rate is based on the work being strictly interior fit out and may be changed by
Modification if the scope is changed to include exterior work such as roof, terrace, windows, exterior wall, etc.);
The derivation of the Change Order markup percentages above shall not be subject to audit by Owner; provided,
however, the Direct Work Increase and application of the above mark-up percentages for any given Change Order
shall be subject to audit by Owner unless and until any lump sum amount is agreed upon as compensation for such
Change Order. 
