§ 12.6 Final Completion and Final Payment
§ 12.6.1 Upon receipt of a final Application for Payment, the Architect will inspect the Work. When the Architect
finds the Work acceptable and the Contract fully performed, the Architect will promptly issue a final Certificate for
Payment.
§ 12.6.2 Final payment shall not become due until the Contractor submits to the Architect releases and waivers of
liens, and data establishing payment or satisfaction of of mechanic’s liens filed by Subcontractors or suppliers to
Contractor’s obligations, such as receipts, claims, security interests, or encumbrances arising out of the Contract and
the Work paid for by Owner.
§ 12.6.3 Acceptance of final payment by the Contractor, a subcontractor or supplier shall constitute a waiver of
claims by that payee except for third party bodily injury and property damage claims and those claims previously
made in writing and identified by that payee as unsettled at the time of final Application for Payment.
§ 12.7 FAILURE OF PAYMENT
§ 12.7.1 If the Owner should fail to pay the Contractor as set forth in Section 4.1, then the Contractor may suspend
the Work until payment of the amount owing has been received after providing the Owner written notice and an
opportunity to cure at least ten (10) days before the intended suspension.
ARTICLE 13 PROTECTION OF PERSONS AND PROPERTY
§ 13.1 The Contractor shall be responsible for initiating, maintaining and supervising all safety precautions and
programs, including all those required by law in connection with performance of the Contract. The Contractor shall
take reasonable precautions to prevent damage, injury, or loss to employees on the Work and other persons who may
be affected thereby, the Work and materials and equipment to be incorporated therein, and other property at the site
or adjacent thereto. The Contractor shall promptly remedy damage and loss to property caused in whole or in part by
the Contractor, or by anyone for whose acts the Contractor may be liable.
§ 13.2 If reasonable precautions will be inadequate to prevent foreseeable bodily injury or death to persons resulting
from a material or substance, including but not limited to asbestos, polychlorinated biphenyl (PCB), lead paint, toxic
substances, mold, mildew, or other hazardous or contaminated materials (“Hazardous Materials”) encountered on
the site by the Contractor, the Contractor shall, upon recognizing the condition, immediately stop the Work in the
affected area and report the condition to the Owner and Architect. The Contractor shall resume Work in the affected
area upon receipt of a clean letter from the Owner’s consultant. By Change Order, the Contract Time shall be
extended appropriately and the Contract Sum shall be increased in the amount of the Construction Manager’s
reasonable additional costs of shut-down, delay and start-up.
§ 13.3 To the fullest extent permitted by law, the Owner shall indemnify and hold harmless the Contractor and
Subcontractors, and agents and employees of any of them from and against claims, damages, losses and expenses,
including but not limited to attorneys' fees, arising out of or resulting from performance thee Work in the affected
area if in fact the Hazardous Material presents the risk of bodily injury or death as described in 13.2 and has not
been rendered harmless, regardless of whether or not such loss or expenses is caused in part by a party indemnified
hereunder.
ARTICLE 14 CORRECTION OF WORK
§ 14.1 The Contractor shall promptly correct Work rejected by the Architect as failing to conform to the
requirements of the Contract Documents. The Contractor shall bear the cost of correcting such rejected Work,
including the costs of uncovering, replacement, and additional testing.
§ 14.2 In addition to the Contractor’s other obligations including warranties under the Contract, the Contractor shall,
for a period of one year after Substantial Completion, correct work not conforming to the requirements of the
Contract Documents.
§ 14.3 If the Contractor fails to correct nonconforming Work within a reasonable time, the Owner may correct it in
accordance with Section 7.3. 
